Description: Five head studies, on white ground: from left to right, man with turban in profile to right, veiled man facing front, man turned to right, bearded man, bare-headed, and bearded man in profile to left wearing skullcap; illustration to Denon's 'Voyage dans la Basse et la Haute Egypte' (Paris, 1802), volume I, plate 107. c.1799/1802 Etching
Producer name: Print made by: Baron Dominique Vivant Denon
Curator's comments: Engraved for Denon's 'Voyage dans la Basse et la Haute Egypte', see 1952,0405.104.
